title: The Spanish Gardener (1956) Dirk Bogarde Bernard Lee
description:
A high ranking diplomat is given a minor posting in the Spanish outback; it seems that the failure of his marriage has also cast aspersions on his professional abilities. Worse, his sense of disappointment causes him to neglect his young son, who is with him. the boy befriends the gardener and discovers the colourful world that is Spain - alas, the father takes exception even to this...

In segmented mpg format, plays on VLC
